Apr 13 2008 	Sadly Disappointed	I'd read the reviews but thought maybe some people were looking for a 'normal business hotel' which was why they were disapponted with The Hempel. Sadly not. My husband chose the hotel as it was one he'd always wanted to stay in. It was to be our first night away together for over 4 years since having children. He booked it directly with the hotel &amp; we thought we were getting a garden view. The hotel is impressive from the outside, the gardens are impressive and the staff were efficient. The reception area is amazing but that's where it stops. We were so disappointed with our 'executive' room. It was at the rear of the building which meant we looked over buildings &amp; back gardens. It was a good size but worn &amp; shabby. The black painted mini bar was chipped with white showing through. The items outside the mini bar (hangover cure remedies etc) looked like they'd be on display for years. The bed looked impressive as it was huge but the sheets had holes that had been darned. It turned out our massive bed was actually two beds joined together so we ended up sleeping on our own beds! The bathroom was functional if you were 6 foot tall (I couldn't reach the mirror) &amp; the shower was fine once I worked out the taps. The toilet paper was very cheap. There was a bowl with cotton wool in &amp; when I lifted it, it was full of dust so clearly hadn't been replaced for a while. I saw no DVD player, no oxygen canisters &amp; no candles in the room. I did like the mood lighting though. The bath robe was not soft &amp; the complimentary slippers were a joke - so cheap &amp; tacky.We had a dreadful night sleep as it was so noisy. We were 3 rooms away from the lift but heard it pinging all night long. We were in an end room which had interconnecting doors with our neighbour. At 5.30am they had a wake up call &amp; so did we - could hear every word. The doors are huge &amp; our neighbours banged there's twice as they were leaving. My husband found the bed too soft.We had the continental breakfast which was fine. It was nice to see the designer features in the dining room although once again the black furniture was chipped.So to summarise the hotel is beginning to look run down &amp; for the price I believe there are better places to stay in London.	
