d hold it in order to do the business at hand. (Yes, really – see the photo.)Shoddy, shoddy, shoddy: Something about minimalist design – it must be executed very well or it just looks bad. Well, you guessed it – this place looks bad. See the other photos for an idea. (I ran out of time to take more pictures – there were many more examples.) The execution of this place is just terrible.Obsequious incompetence: The staff ranged from fawning to couldn’t-care-less, but there was one common denominator: incompetence. I could go on and on – but you get the idea.Were this a two or three star hotel priced at a reasonable rate, that would be one thing. But at the rate of £250-300 per night, to say it’s not worth it would be more than just English understatement.	
