Jul 13 2006	Not that special was disappointed	Don't be fooled by all the hype, the Hempel is NOT that special. I stayed there for two nights at the end of June on a romantic retreat, and considering the amount of money we spent I was not that impressed. When we tried to check in we were told our room wasn't ready, as were the other two people in line behind us - despite the fact it was after the designated check in time. (As we checked out we heard new arrivals being told the same thing.) The room itself was fairly small and dark, and the furniture and decor was shabby. I know it's a minimalist hotel, but a shabbily painted white room with only a bed in it is taking the micky, in my opinion. We had a small lounge area facing out onto a row of flats, so couldn't open the blinds as our neighbours would be able to see right into our room. The flat screen TV was attached to the wall in the little lounge area, and so we could not watch TV in bed. Neither was the sofa big enough for two adults to lie on, so we ended up laying half on the coffee table and half on the sofa in order to watch TV... hardly what you expect when paying over 200 quid a night. On the plus side, the room had a decent enough stereo (although no remote control) and a massive bathtub (easily big enough for two). The location is good for nightlife in Notting Hill. The staff were very friendly too.	
